result.name: Gyu Jin

reviews.text: Responsive waiters and waitress. Food quality is good but ice-cream is low at stock. Price appropriate. No waiting time on Sunday afternoon.

A simple, basic Japanese hot-pot lunch set with one dish of meat (beef or pork) and soup base, the assorted vegetable, meat balls, rice, 8 favours Haagen Dazs ice-cream as dessert would be subject to as much as you want at a value of $89.   Lovely.

Very good and attentive service. Had a mix of Teppanyaki and Sashimi. Everything was executed to perfection. Fish presented before cutting the Sashimi, fresh from the market. Meat very good and deliciously tasty. Chefs listening closely to the guests wishes. Will definitely return here.

Many Ingredients to choose from for your hot pot. You can have as many refills as you'd like via the small screen at your table. Service is fast and blunt. Not too fond of the yuzu soup base, it was like jam with salty broth. Meat and veggies were fresh and tasty. Would have liked more non-dairy desserts for option.

I wanted to visit this restaurant tonight with my family so I made reservation the day before. We  arrived 4 people, my husband and me, and our 2 children 9 and 3 years old. After the staff ( almost nobody speaks English) brought us to our table we made the order and clarified the price for 2 adult portion, 1 child portion and baby portion for free. This was the typical offer as we know it also from other all-you-can eat hot pot restaurants. However, few minutes later when we just wanted to start eating, the staff came back, pointing to our 9-years old boy, repeating something in Chinese, then pointing again on the price list, showing  the adult price. Then starting pointing on our little girl  (who eat almost nothing except of few noodles) asking her to pay for child portion. Since the restaurant was not yet full, in a short time there were  5-6 staff around us , talking loud in Chinese , or very pure English, pulling our boy to the entrance with a measuring tape to find out how tall he was, since they had a limit of 140cm, from that they counted the full price. He was about 2 cm taller then 140. Our argument, that inspite of he is a very tall European boy, but still a  CHILD, eating child portions, the staff was just continuing asking for adult price for him and child price for baby-girl. It was so disgusting, the whole restaurant was watching us. To us it was a clear case of discrimination. Most of Asian 9-years old boys are at least 10 cm shorter than our boy. The size of him doesn’t tell anything about his eating behaviour. However, if a restaurant chooses such strange criteria to measuring its guests, they should do it BEFORE they bring the guests to their table and agree a different price , and they should do in DISCRETION , not in this humiliating way. Our boy felt so ashamed, so sad. I don’t understand how can somebody treat a child like this. Anyway, after this bad experience, we left the restaurant without eating. They should know, it’s not about paying the higher price, it’s about treating the customer in a human great full way. So, if you want to enjoy your dinner in a restaurant with polite and friendly staff, you should NOT choose this one.

Responsive waiters and waitress. Food quality is good but ice-cream is low at stock. Price appropriate. No waiting time on Sunday afternoon.
食物質素一般，服務員態度有好大改善空間。

早起的鳥兒有得食！
5:00前兩個人去食90分鐘，時間算夠，最緊要少人，舒服。日式湯底好，我選$179特選牛豬肉任叫，可能早，上菜爽快，出面任夾的，我重視的是鮮菜，合格。其他的乏善足陳，另外飲品雪糕任取，整體滿意。
